INSERT INTO public."Recipe" (title,image,"userId",categories,ingredients,story,description,"createdAt","updatedAt","deletedAt") VALUES
	 ('Pasta with Sausage, Basil, and Mustard','recipes-pasta-sausage-basil-and-mustard.webp',1,'{Pasta,Beef}','{"1 pound penne"," rigatoni"," or medium shells","1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil","8 hot Italian sausages"," meat removed from casings and crumbled (about 1 1/2 pounds)","3/4 cup dry white wine","3/4 cup heavy cream","3 tablespoons grainy mustard","Pinch of crushed red pepper","1 cup thinly sliced basil"}','In 2018, Food & Wine named this recipe one of our 40 best. The pasta with sausage and mustard is perfect for a cool fall or winter evening and comes together quickly, so it''s as suited for a busy weeknight as it is a cozy weekend. Don''t be suspicious of the dish''s flavor combination; although grainy mustard, spicy sausage, crisp white wine, and fragrant basil may seem like an odd assortment to accompany pasta, the finished product is greater than the sum of its parts, a synchronized medley of tastes and textures that you''ll be craving again and again.

Not only is this sausage pasta recipe fast to prepare, it necessitates just a handful of ingredients, many of which you likely already have. Any medium-sized pasta shape will do, though you''ll want to use one with adequate nooks and crannies for hanging onto the creamy mustard sauce. For even speedier prep, buy Italian sausage patties instead of links to save you the trouble of removing the casings. You''ll use less than a cup of wine here, which is a great way to polish off an open bottle if you happen to have one in the fridge. Fresh basil is the only thing you''ll need to slice; don''t skimp on it — it provides both flavor and pops of color to the mustard pasta.','<ul><li><p>Gather ingredients.</p></li><li><p>Cook the pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water until al dente and then drain.</p></li><li><p>Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a large, deep skillet. Add the sausage meat and brown over moderately high heat, about 5 minutes.</p></li><li><p>Add the wine and simmer, scraping up the browned bits from the bottom, until reduced by half, about 5 minutes.</p></li><li><p>Add the cream, mustard, and crushed red pepper and simmer for 2 minutes.</p></li><li><p>Remove the skillet from the heat, add the pasta and basil, and toss to coat.</p></li><li><p>Serve at once.</p></li></ul>','2025-03-09 05:47:45.886',NULL,NULL),
	 ('Dirty Martini Baked Potatoes','dirty-martini-baked-potatoes.webp',1,'{"Side Dishes"}','{"4 large (about 12 ounces each) russet potatoes"," scrubbed and patted dry","1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil","2 1/4 teaspoons kosher salt"," divided","1/2 teaspoon black pepper"," plus more for garnish","3/4 cup pitted Castelvetrano olives"," quartered lengthwise"," plus 1/3 cup olive brine","1/4 cup (2 ounces) gin (such as Beefeater)","1 tablespoon dry vermouth","3 strips lemon peel","1/4 cup heavy cream","4 ounces cream cheese"," softened","5 ounces creamy blue cheese"," crumbled (about 1 cup)","1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh chives"," plus more for garnish","1/2 cup plus 6 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese"," divided"}','Twice-baked potatoes and Dirty Martinis have one thing in common: They’re both classics. Here Russet potatoes make for a double-the-fun dinner when matched up with Dirty Martini Dip. Combining the fluffy potato flesh with cream cheese and sharp blue cheese creates a meltingly tender filling that contrasts with the crisp, salty potato skins. A splash of reserved liquid from the boozy olive brine seals in the signature dirty martini flavor while balancing the potatoes’ richness. Need a bite-size version perfect for an appetizer? Try our mini version on for size at your next gathering. ','<p><strong>Step 1</strong></p><p>Preheat oven to 425°F; position oven rack in center of oven about 7- to 8-inches away from heating element. Pierce potatoes all over with a fork and place on a foil-lined baking sheet. Rub potatoes with olive oil and season with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Bake until fork-tender, about 1 hour. Let sit until cool enough to handle but still hot, about 15 minutes. Increase oven temperature to broil.</p><p></p><p><strong>Step 2</strong></p><p>While potatoes bake, place olives, olive brine, gin, vermouth, and lemon peel strips in a small jar or airtight container. Seal container and shake well to combine. Chill in refrigerator until flavors meld, at least 30 minutes and up to 24 hours. Strain marinated olives using a fine-mesh sieve set over a medium bowl, reserving olives and brine mixture separately. Finely chop 1/4 cup of the olives; set aside.</p><p></p><p><strong>Step 3</strong></p><p>Once potatoes are cool enough to handle, slice open in center, leaving 1/2-inch unsliced on each side. Push ends of potatoes with your fingers to help open centers.&nbsp; Using a spoon, scoop most of the flesh from the potatoes into a large bowl, leaving a 1/4-inch layer of flesh on the skin. Return potato shells to foil-lined baking sheet and gently open potatoes slightly more to help when filling. Season insides with 1/2 teaspoon of the remaining salt; set aside.</p><p></p><p><strong>Step 4</strong></p><p>To potato flesh in large bowl, add cream, cream cheese, blue cheese, chives, 1/4 cup of the reserved olive brine mixture, 1/2 cup of the Parmesan, and remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt. Using a potato masher, mash potato mixture until well combined. Taste and stir in additional brine mixture, if desired. Spoon or pipe potato mixture evenly into potato skins on baking sheet, piling high as needed until filling is all used up. Sprinkle each evenly with 1 1/2 tablespoons Parmesan.</p><p></p><p><strong>Step 5</strong></p><p>Broil until warmed through and cheese is melted and golden brown, 6 to 8 minutes. Transfer to a platter and top evenly with finely chopped marinated olives. Garnish with chives and black pepper and serve immediately. Reserve remaining marinated olives and brine for another use.</p>','2025-03-09 06:02:07.107',NULL,NULL),
	 ('Nasi Goreng Kencur Kemangi','nasi-goreng-kencur.webp',1,'{"Breakfast & Brunch"}','{"1 piring nasi putih","1 ikat daun kemangi petiki daunnya","1/2 sdt kaldu bubuk","Secukupnya kecap manis","dan saus tomat (optional)","Secukupnya minyak goreng untuk menumis","2 buah cabai rawit","sesuai selera","5 siung bawang merah","3 siung bawang putih","1 ruas kencur","1/2 sdt garam halus","Secukupnya teri goreng","kerupuk dll"}','Ceritanya sdh lama ga makan nasgor, si bocil minta dibikini.','<ul><li><p>Siapkan nasi dan bumbu halus. Cuci bersih daun kemangi, tiriskan.</p></li><li><p>Tumis bumbu halus hingga wangi, masukan nasi lalu beri kecap manis, saus tomat dan kaldu bubuk, aduk rata. Masak hingga nasi tercampur rata dengan bumbu. Koreksi rasanya.</p></li><li><p>Masukkan daun kemangi aduk rata sebentar. Matikan api. Siapkan di piring, taburi dengan teri goreng.</p></li></ul>','2025-03-20 07:45:05.289',NULL,NULL),
	 ('Chicken Fajitas','Chicken-Fajitas.webp',2,'{Chicken}','{"1/4 cup / 65 ml lime juice","1/4 cup / 65 ml orange juice","2 tbsp olive oil","2 garlic cloves","1 tsp cumin powder","1 tsp salt","1/2 tsp black pepper","700g / 1.2 lb skinless chicken thighs or 2 large chicken breasts","2 tbsp olive oil","3 capsicums / bell peppers","1 large onion","8– 12 small tortillas","1 large avocado","Sour cream","Fresh lime wedges"}','Whenever I see rainbow coloured capsicum on sale at the stores, I immediately think of Fajitas.\r\n\r\nI know, I know, full points for (un)originality.\r\n\r\nThough to be fair, when I see just redcapsicum on sale, my first thought is the not so well known Spanish Romesco Sauce. The magic chargrilled capsicum-almond sauce that I use as a dip / sauce / marinade that I am abnormally addicted to.\r\n','<p><strong>Preparation:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Place Marinade ingredients in a large bowl and mix. Add chicken, toss well to coat. Marinade for 1 hour to 24 hours (or freeze immediately then defrost overnight).</p></li><li><p>Use 2 skillets to cook the chicken and vegetables at the same time, if you can.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Vegetables:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Heat 1 tbsp oil in a heavy based skillet over high heat until smoking. Add vegetables to cover the base of the pan in a single layer without too much overlapping (I cook in 3 batches). Spread out, leave for 45 seconds (to char it).</p></li><li><p>Toss quickly then spread out. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Leave 45 seconds, toss then spread out, then leave 45 seconds. Remove onto platter and repeat with remaining Vegetables.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Chickens:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large skillet over medium high heat. Add chicken and cook for 3 to 4 minutes until caramelised. Turn and cook the other side for 3 – 4 minutes.</p></li><li><p>Remove onto a plate, cover loosely with foil. Rest for 3 minutes then slice.</p></li></ul><p><strong>To Serve:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Warm tortillas using chosen method.</p></li><li><p>Pile peppers and onion onto tortilla. Top with chicken, drizzle with sour cream, squeeze over lime juice. Fold, devour and be happy.</p></li></ul>','2025-03-24 10:53:25.661',NULL,NULL);
